Rio Tinto-Zinc Corp Plc &lt;RTZL.L> cut itsbalance sheet gearing, measured as net debt as a proportion ofequity, to 35 pct at the end of 1986 from 61 pct a yearearlier, finance director Andrew Buxton told reporters.    He said currency movements last year did not greatly affectthe earnings outcome, though had a greater impact on thebalance sheet.    At year-end, 40 pct of its assets were industrial, 35 pctin metal mining and processing and 25 pct in energy.    Earlier, RTZ reported 1986 net attributable profit of 245mln stg against 257 mln the previous year. Reuter&#3;